    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1912-10-30T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1912-10-30T00:00:00-05:00" n="1800"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1800">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 767.70/41.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                            <gloss type="to">American Minister to Roumania</gloss>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram—Paraphrase.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1912-10-30">
                            <hi rend="italic">October 30, 1912</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>The request of Bulgaria conveyed in your telegram of the 21st is being
                    considered. The Department’s decision will be sent you by <pb facs="1460"
                        n="1344" xml:id="pg_1344"/> telegraph. Meanwhile yon may say, if pressed for
                    a reply, that this Government has not thus far found it necessary to make any
                    further or more formal declaration of neutrality, in view of the comprehensive
                    provisions of the Neutrality Act: see Revised Statutes, sections 5281 to 5291,
                    both inclusive.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Knox.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
